sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User (run_pipeline.py)
    participant B as build.py (orchestrator)
    participant RAW as Raw GSJ data (read-only)
    participant BND as boundaries.py
    participant SHP as shapefile_io.py
    participant GEO as geo_utils.py
    participant INF as InferenceEngine (inference.py)
    participant KB as Knowledge base (L1-L4 + sources)
    participant PA as pdf_assets.py
    participant PT as pdf_text.py
    participant OUT as Database & outputs

    U->>B: build()

    Note over B,BND: Stage 3 - region boundaries
    B->>BND: compute() + write()
    BND->>RAW: read geo_A.shp extents
    BND-->>OUT: region_boundaries.yaml + review.md

    loop each sheet (08062 / 08063 / 08074)
        Note over B,SHP: Stage 1 - vector extraction
        B->>SHP: read_shapefile(geo_A.shp)
        SHP->>RAW: parse .shp / .dbf / .prj (Shift-JIS / UTF-8)
        SHP-->>B: shapes + attribute records + CRS

        loop each polygon
            Note over B: Stage 6 - normalize
            B->>B: normalize(rec, field profile)
            B->>GEO: polygon_area_m2 / centroid (Stage 2)
            GEO-->>B: area, centroid

            alt new distinct unit
                Note over B,KB: Stage 7 - layered inference
                B->>INF: infer(unit, asset_refs)
                INF->>KB: L1 geology ID (rock/soil, age, consolidation)
                INF->>KB: L2 translate to geotech ground type + terms
                INF->>KB: L3 indicative properties (+ citable sources)
                INF->>KB: L4 considerations + recommended investigation
                INF-->>B: L1-L4 chain + risk flags + confidence
            end
        end
    end

    Note over B,PT: Stages 4-5 - PDF assets & text
    B->>PA: build()
    PA->>RAW: read explanatory PDFs (JPEG / JPEG2000)
    PA->>PT: extract_pdf() for text + quality score
    PT-->>PA: text blocks + readability flag
    PA-->>OUT: pdf_asset_index (+ PNG previews, clustering summary)

    Note over B,OUT: Stage 8 - persist
    B->>OUT: write_gpkg / write_sqlite / write_csv / write_json
    OUT-->>U: GeoPackage, SQLite, inference_chains.json, CSVs

    Note over U,OUT: Later - interactive use (Stage 9)
    U->>OUT: query_point(lat, lon)  [query.py]
    OUT->>GEO: point_in_polygon / distance_to_boundary
    OUT-->>U: unit + full L1-L4 drill-down chain
